For packages that provide a single API it could look something like this:

``` json
{
  "name": "frobnicator",
  "version": "1.2.3",
  "apiVersion": "1.0.0",
}
```

And for multiple APIs it could look like this:

``` json
{
  "name": "frobnicator",
  "version": "1.2.3",
  "apiVersion": {
    "frob": "1.1.0",
    "xyzzy": "2.2.0"
  }
}
```

I suppose that this can easily be done with a little bit of code, but making this a standard and having the code live in Atom Core would be helpful to package developers.
